# Microsoft 365 Identity & User Management Home Lab

## Overview
This project demonstrates foundational Microsoft 365 administration skills using the Microsoft 365 Admin Center. It simulates real-world IT tasks such as user management, group creation, license assignment, role-based access control, and basic helpdesk operations.

This lab was completed using the Microsoft 365 Admin Center, which is used by IT administrators in real organizations to manage users, identities, and services.

---

## Objectives
- Create and manage user accounts
- Create and configure security groups
- Assign and manage Microsoft 365 licenses
- Assign administrative roles
- Perform basic helpdesk tasks (password reset, user management)
- Demonstrate identity lifecycle management

---

## Tools Used
- Microsoft 365 Admin Center

---

## Lab Summary

In this lab, I performed the following tasks:

- Created multiple test users (Admin, Helpdesk, Standard User)
- Configured security groups for role-based access control
- Assigned Microsoft 365 licenses to users
- Assigned administrative roles (Global Admin, Helpdesk Admin)
- Simulated helpdesk tasks such as password resets and account management
- Practiced user lifecycle operations (create, modify, block, delete users)

---

## Key Skills Demonstrated

- Identity and Access Management (IAM)
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
- SaaS administration (Microsoft 365)
- Helpdesk troubleshooting workflows
- User lifecycle management
- Security group management

---

## Key Learnings

- Groups simplify large-scale user management in enterprise environments
- Licenses control access to Microsoft 365 services
- Admin roles must follow the principle of least privilege
- Helpdesk workflows are essential for account recovery and support
- Identity management is a core function in all IT environments

